  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to test whether the provision of ONS to malnourished children
      across Europe, in addition to standard counselling, will improve weight gain and other
      outcomes.

      The hypothesis to be tested is:

      • Supplementation with ONS in malnourished paediatric patients will lead to increased WFH
      gain, as well as less malnutrition related complications (e.g. infections).

      Primary outcome • The change in BMI z-score over the intervention period of 3 months

      Secondary outcomes

      • The change in WFH-weight for height (z-scores) over the intervention period of 3 months
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
